  "body": "Hi\r\nI have the following type:\r\n```\r\nimport { InputFacet1, InputFacet2} from '../typechain-types';\r\ntype Facets = InputFacet1 & InputFacet2;\r\n```\r\nthen using the `hardhat-diamond-abi` I combine all facets abis into one file:\r\n```\r\nconst allFacets = (await ethers.getContractAt(abi, Diamond.address)) as BaseContract as Facets;\r\n```\r\n`allFacets` have type of `Facets` which is correct. but when I connect to a different runner:\r\n```\r\nconst changedAccount = allFacets.connect(acc2);\r\n```\r\nnow `changedAccount` type is `InputFacet1` and not the `Facets`.\r\nAlso the typechain type for connect() method becomes this:\r\n`connect(runner?: ContractRunner | null): InputFacet1;`\r\n\r\nIt seems that `.connect()` returns the contract with the first type of the combination.",
