    "body": "The problem here is that the types of the contracts are something like this:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\ntype Lock = {\r\n  connect(...): Lock\r\n}\r\n\r\ntype Lock2 = {\r\n  connect(...): Lock2\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo when you do `type Lock1AndLock2 = Lock1 & Lock2`, the resulting type has a `connect(...): Lock` function (the first one \"wins\").\r\n\r\nMaybe if typechain returned `this` for those types this would work, but that needs some testing. I suggest opening and issue in the typechain repo about this, because there isn't much we can do on Hardhat's side.\r\n\r\nTentatively closing, I'll re-open if there is something we can do on our side.",
